  "explanation": [
    "Lens Maker's Formula: <katex>$\\frac{1}{f} = (\\mu_{rel} - 1)(\\frac{2}{R})$</katex>.",
    "In air: <katex>$\\frac{1}{f_a} = (1.5 - 1)K = 0.5K \\Rightarrow f_a = \\frac{1}{0.5K} = \\frac{2}{K}$</katex>.",
    "In water: <katex>$\\mu_{rel} = \\frac{1.5}{4/3} = \\frac{4.5}{4} = \\frac{9}{8} = 1.125$</katex>.",
    "<katex>$\\frac{1}{f_w} = (\\frac{9}{8} - 1)K = \\frac{1}{8}K \\Rightarrow f_w = \\frac{8}{K}$</katex>.",
    "<katex>$\\frac{f_w}{f_a} = \\frac{8/K}{2/K} = 4$</katex>. So <katex>$f_w = 4 f_a$</katex>.",
    "Change is <katex>$f_w - f_a = 3f_a$</katex>. Percentage increase = <katex>$\\frac{3f_a}{f_a} \\times 100\\% = 300\\%$</katex>."
